description:
&lt;p&gt;Shropshire Community Health NHS Trust positively encourages applications from all areas of the community, regardless of age, gender, ethnicity, disability, sexual orientation or religious beliefs. We are committed to ensuring people who work for the community trust have a good working life - and a good work life/home life balance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an opportunity to join our Financial Accounts Team in Shropshire Community Health NHS Trust, we are Future Focus Finance Level 1 accredited team and the Trust is accredited as a CIMA Development Quality Partner.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Reporting to the Financial Accountant, the successful candidate will be responsible for ensuring that supplier invoices and credit notes are processed promptly and accurately in accordance with the trust’s Standing Financial Instructions (SFIs) and detailed financial procedures. They will also need to have good interpersonal skills and be able to communicate with a number of people in and outside the organization. Responding to queries from managers and customers on the telephone/email, providing assistance and advice as required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;AS A MANDATORY PART OF THE RECRUITMENT PROCESS YOU SHOULD ANSWER THE FOLLOWING QUESTION IN YOUR SUPPORTING STATEMENT (maximum of 200 words)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you were in a difficult conversation with a supplier regarding a price query on an invoice, please list the steps you would take to try and resolve the issue?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Contact Name: Michael Hill&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone: 01743 277500&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact: Mr Michael Hill (Senior Financial Accountant) via michael.hill4@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
